<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=101323931375152></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101323931375152><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=11&mid=101323931375152>Int. VS. manna</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=11&mid=101323931375152#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=142715><span id= >stefaan</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>1 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Feb 9th 3:24 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>is there a ratio that exists for int. to manna and vice versa?&nbsp;&nbsp;(i.e. a +2 int. ring = 30 manna or a 30 manna ring = +2 int).  i am wondering if i should find +int items or +manna items.  <br><br>i currently have 2 moonstone rings (30 manna each) and dont know if i should ditch em and wear 2 - +2 int. rings.  which would give me more torque (manna)<br><br>thanks<br>stef<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
