	   <tr><td colspan=2>A wizard gets a lot more spells than that (which will get quite expensive after a while). Atr L5 there is 14 spells you can have, all of them are sold at vendors. You can find infos about them at<br><br><a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/spells/spells.asp?Class=Wizard" target=_new>http://eq.castersrealm.com/spells/spells.asp?Class=Wizard</a><br><br>The wizard bible is at <a href="http://www.graffe.com/" target=_new>http://www.graffe.com/</a> , you can get a lot of insight at that site.<br><br>Depending on your race you will need to look for a hunting ground where you get good loot, your L1 spells are like 1pp total, your L5 spells are 4pp total, your L8 spells run to like 30pp.<br><br>A good choice are the orcs in West Commons, they sometimes drop Pickbringers Chainmail Coifs, that sell for 23+ pp at merchants and get you a long way to affording your spells.<br>&nbsp;<br>Nindor<br>L52 Dwarven Cleric on Zebuxoruk</td></tr>
